        "timestamp": "2019-05-31 12:41:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI don't understand the commit message. How come we got RPMs earlier? There was no \"full control\"? What have changed?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "a02253d8a0dd9cf508d733682b1579bbf8ed50ce",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5000,
          "name": "Tom�? Levora",
          "display_name": "Tomáš Levora",
          "email": "tomas.levora@gmail.com",
          "username": "Tomas.Levora"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-31 13:01:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> I don't understand the commit message. How come we got RPMs earlier? There was no \"full control\"? What have changed?\n\nIt was part of to the download script before and it fully deppended on the build system what was downloaded by the yum-downloader etc. So this is probably better way to control it.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "d8b84d5af557dffa982f7dfcd13b38331870bceb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4009,
          "name": "Michal Ptacek",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "m.ptacek@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "Michal.Ptacek"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-05-31 13:59:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I don't understand the commit message. How come we got RPMs\n > earlier? There was no \"full control\"? What have changed?\npreviously no versions were specified and just subset of packages were downloaded, dependencies were collected using --resolve argument for yumdownloader. Issues like different dependencies between build & install server might occurs",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "18862c6578f8d97a73e04636e1af62fa2693968d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-06-03 06:22:19.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > I don't understand the commit message. How come we got RPMs\n>  > earlier? There was no \"full control\"? What have changed?\n> previously no versions were specified and just subset of packages were downloaded, dependencies were collected using --resolve argument for yumdownloader. Issues like different dependencies between build & install server might occurs\n\nPretty amazing. Luckily it looks normal now.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
